frameDefinitions: An Agent begins preventing a Captive from moving despite a tendency or desire on the part of the Captive to do so.
The Authorities hold a Suspect under suspicion of having committed a crime (Charges).
In this frame an Agent continues to possess a Theme for a Duration of time. '' 'In her heart she must retain bitterness against those who had killed him.'
A Fugitive avoids recapture by or on the authority of Authorities in relation to a Crime which the Fugitive has committed or is suspected of having committed.
The words in this frame have to do with people and the personal Relationships they are or can be a part of.
frameExamples: Authorities recently <t>captured</t> several suspects who were hiding in a remote mountain area.
The police <t>held</t> Mr. Smith in the slammer on charges of killing his lawyer.
In her heart she must <t>retain</t> bitterness against those who had killed him.
He is in fact a <t>fugitive</t> of the law and you must inform the police if you see him.
And of course that drippy <t><fex name='Partner_1'>boyfriend</fex></t> of hers backed her up.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient entity which is responsible for restricting the movement or location of the <fen>Captive</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event occurs.
This role identifies the person who is taken into custody and held, under suspicion of having committed a crime.
The person who has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity which the <fen>Agent</fen> possesses for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Fugitive</fen> has escaped and/or is evading capture by law enforcement <fen>Authorities</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Fugitive</fen> is evading law enforcement.
This role identifies the general <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Fugitive</fen> is located.
That partner in the <fen>Relationship</fen> who is realized as the subject of verbs in active form sentences, or of adjectives in predicative uses.
That partner in the <fen>Relationship</fen> who is not expressed as the external argument.
The joint construal of both <fen>Partners</fen> in the <fen>Relationship</fen>.
